<emphasis id="F5A2EAEDFF873425FF590367FE04D631" bold="true" box="[192,317,1539,1563]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="00D64D7CFF873425FED20360FD51D631" authorityName="Gordon &amp; González" authorityYear="2011" box="[331,616,1539,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="esmeraldas">
<emphasis id="F5A2EAEDFF873425FED20360FD51D631" box="[331,616,1539,1563]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Hyperaspis esmeraldas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a dorsal color pattern similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="00D64D7CFF873425FB1D0360FE0FD611" authority="Gordon and Canepari" authorityName="Gordon and Canepari" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="howdeni">
<emphasis id="F5A2EAEDFF873425FB1D0360FA30D631" box="[1156,1289,1539,1563]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">H howdeni</emphasis>
Gordon and Canepari
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="00D64D7CFF873425FED80340FDFAD611" authority="Gordon and Canepari" authorityName="Gordon and Canepari" box="[321,707,1571,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chocoi">
<emphasis id="F5A2EAEDFF873425FED80340FE6ED611" box="[321,343,1572,1595]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5A2EAEDFF873425FEFD0347FE89D611" box="[356,432,1571,1595]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">chocoi</emphasis>
Gordon and Canepari
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="00D64D7CFF873425FC9B0340FBA1D611" authority="Gordon and Canepari" authorityName="Gordon and Canepari" box="[770,1176,1571,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="istmina">
<emphasis id="F5A2EAEDFF873425FC9B0340FC21D611" box="[770,792,1572,1595]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5A2EAEDFF873425FCBF0340FCBCD611" box="[806,901,1572,1595]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">istmina</emphasis>
Gordon and Canepari
</taxonomicName>
, couplet 
<quantity id="002E9B1AFF873425FA9B0347FA06D611" box="[1282,1343,1571,1595]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.826" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" unit="in" value="19.0">19 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="A3474B0EFF873425FADD0347FEFAD671" author="Gordon, R. D. &amp; C. Canepari" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" pagination="245 - 512" refId="ref7630" refString="Gordon, R. D., and C. Canepari. 2008. South American Coccinellidae (Coleoptera), Part XI: a systematic revision of Hyperaspidini (Hyperaspidinae). Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; G. Doria &quot; XCIX: 245 - 512." type="book chapter" year="2008">Gordon and Canepari (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. Genitalia distinguish it from the former two species, both of which have nearly straight basal lobes with reduced lateral projections. It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="00D64D7CFF873425FBC60300FBD9D651" box="[1119,1248,1636,1659]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="istmina">
<emphasis id="F5A2EAEDFF873425FBC60300FB4CD651" box="[1119,1141,1636,1659]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F5A2EAEDFF873425FB1B0300FBD9D651" box="[1154,1248,1636,1659]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">istmina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by smaller size, reduced macula on each elytron, and intercoxal carinae widely separated at apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8FCC6574FF873425FF5903A7FD85D6D1" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C76936FFFF873425FF5903A7FD85D6D1" blockId="9.[192,1441,1731,1787]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis id="F5A2EAEDFF873425FF5903A7FE6DD6F1" bold="true" box="[192,340,1731,1755]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species is named for 
<collectingRegion id="0512F81DFF873425FD1503A7FCA8D6F1" box="[652,913,1731,1755]" country="Ecuador" name="Esmeraldas" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Esmeraldas Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="BFC1766FFF873425FC0303A7FB3AD6F1" box="[922,1027,1731,1755]" name="Ecuador" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, where the 
<typeStatus id="186D885DFF873425FB1503A7FBCDD6F1" box="[1164,1268,1731,1755]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected. The name is used as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
